text:
I love that @UPS gives their drivers the decision-making ability to determine if a package can not be delivered without a signature, even if the sender stated 'no signature required.' I live in the whitest suburb and get 8+ packages delivered each week #annoyed
@UPSHelp
@roetravw Our driver's first priority is keeping packages safe. We have a service called UPS MyChoice where you can leave delivery settings for your packages.  ^MS https://t.co/BPZKndqww1

@UPSHelp What criteria is used when keeping packages safe?  i came home to three other packages from different logistics companies, your logic makes no sense.  MyChoice also wants to assess me a fee sending a message to the dirver.  huh?
@roetravw There are no fees for driver instructions. ^ZM https://t.co/wKJHDXWGRQ
